Regression is a method used to identify the relationship between input and output variables. In a regression problem, we are given a set of noisy measurements (or output data) $\mathbf{y} = [y_1, \dots, y_d]^T$, which are affected by measurement noise $\boldsymbol{\eta} = [\eta_1, \dots, \eta_d]^T$.
